## Mapping Domain Events to UI Events (Web Layer)

**Web layer bridges domain events to HTMX-friendly UI events:**

```csharp
// Web/Events/SwapEventChains.cs
public static class SwapEventChains
{
    public static void Register(ISwapEvents events)
    {
        // Todo events
        events.Chain(
            DomainEvents.TodoCreated,
            "ui.refreshList",
            "ui.showToast");
        
        events.Chain(
            DomainEvents.TodoUpdated,
            "ui.refreshList",
            "ui.showToast");
        
        events.Chain(
            DomainEvents.TodoDeleted,
            "ui.refreshList",
            "ui.showToast",
            "ui.refreshStats");
        
        events.Chain(
            DomainEvents.TodoCompleted,
            "ui.refreshStats");
        
        // Product events (example)
        events.Chain(
            DomainEvents.ProductCreated,
            "ui.refreshProductList",
            "ui.showToast");
    }
}
```

**IEventBus implementation (adapter):**

```csharp
// Web/Infrastructure/SwapEventBusAdapter.cs
public class SwapEventBusAdapter : IEventBus
{
    private readonly ISwapEvents _swapEvents;
    
    public SwapEventBusAdapter(ISwapEvents swapEvents)
    {
        _swapEvents = swapEvents;
    }
    
    public void Fire(string eventName)
    {
        _swapEvents.Fire(eventName);
    }
    
    public void Fire(string eventName, object data)
    {
        _swapEvents.Fire(eventName, data);
    }
}
```

**Registration:**

```csharp
// Web/Program.cs
builder.Services.AddScoped<IEventBus, SwapEventBusAdapter>();
```

