## Listening to Events in Views

### Basic Listener

```html
<!-- Web/Views/Todos/_TodoList.cshtml -->
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Todos/List"
     hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body"
     hx-swap="outerHTML">
    @foreach (var todo in Model)
    {
        <partial name="_TodoItem" model="todo" />
    }
</div>
```

**Explanation:**
- `hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body"` — Listen for event on `<body>`
- When event fires → `hx-get="/Todos/List"` fetches updated list
- Response replaces entire `#todo-list` content

### Multiple Event Triggers

```html
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Todos/List"
     hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body, 
                 entity.created:todo from:body,
                 entity.updated:todo from:body,
                 entity.deleted:todo from:body">
</div>
```

Or rely on event chain:

```html
<!-- Listens to ALL todo changes via chain -->
<div id="todo-list"
     hx-get="/Todos/List"
     hx-trigger="ui.refreshList from:body">
</div>
```

### Load + Event Trigger

```html
<!-- Load on page load AND when event fires -->
<div id="stats"
     hx-get="/Todos/Stats"
     hx-trigger="load, ui.refreshStats from:body">
</div>
```

